        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Downtown Asheville, or near Weaverville, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Asheville, Weaverville, Mars Hill, B.R. Parkway-East Asheville
To Craggy Gardens, Mount Mitchell State Park, Woodfin, B.R.
Parkway-Craggy To Little Switzerland, Barnardsville, and Flat Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
